description:
When it's my turn to take my son to school, I allow myself to wander around the city center and reflect. When I passed the Japanese Embassy, ​​I decided to look at the Japanese flag in black and white optics. 
I often think that black and white optics provide a lot of possibilities for imagination. If we didn't know that the Japanese flag has a red circle, what color could we imagine it? And what could this color symbolize? Each person could come up with their own color and their own symbol.
